{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0a05c97-39bb-48c0-83f1-92d238ea91d5","content":"Here's what to update across your three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"sdk\": {\n    \"version\": \"11.0.100\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Update base images\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then run:**\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9a2ad640-0de0-4aa6-ad99-57fa50eb8253","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"8869:33166:1EA89BF:221A407:69FA9D30"},"id":"0345769e-c7dd-4948-a5ca-283f2766a1ce","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:45:26.883Z","parentId":"ff8b9a36-8d4f-4660-8833-f9338068ec97"}
